---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import HubCard from '../../../components/HubCard.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="CSS Anti-patterns"
    description="Common CSS architecture mistakes and how LSCSS avoids them."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Anti-patterns</p>
        <p class="summary-badge">Summary Page</p>

        <h1>
            Common CSS anti-patterns
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            Most CSS problems are architectural problems rather than syntax
            problems.
        </p>

        <p class="summary-note">
            This page is a summary. For full examples and fixes, use
            <a href="/learn/anti-pattern-gallery/">Anti-pattern gallery</a>.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <ul>
            <li>specificity spirals</li>
            <li>deep selector nesting</li>
            <li>global leakage</li>
            <li>utility soup</li>
            <li>component coupling</li>
            <li>ID selectors</li>
            <li>layout mixed into components</li>
            <li>uncontained legacy CSS</li>
            <li><code>!important</code> abuse</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Why these happen
        </h2>

        <p>
            Teams often create accidental complexity when architecture is
            missing, inconsistent, or disconnected from platform features.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>Next useful pages</h2>
        <div class="hub-grid">
            <HubCard href="/learn/anti-pattern-gallery/" title="Anti-pattern gallery">
                <p>See practical before/after examples for common architecture failures.</p>
            </HubCard>
            <HubCard href="/apply/decision-trees/" title="Decision trees">
                <p>Use repeatable rules to prevent anti-patterns during implementation.</p>
            </HubCard>
            <HubCard href="/apply/audit-checklist/" title="Audit checklist">
                <p>Review whether known anti-patterns are present in your codebase.</p>
            </HubCard>
        </div>
    </section>
</DocsLayout>
